{"title_page": "All-Party Parliamentary Group for Future Generations", "text_new": "{{multiple issues|\n{{notability|Companies|date=March 2019}}\n{{third-party|date=March 2019}}\n}}\n{{Infobox organization\n| formation = October 2017\n| type = [[All-Party Parliamentary Group]]\n| leader_title = Chair\n| leader_name = [[Bambos Charalambous|Bambos Charalambous MP]]\n| name = All-Party Parliamentary Group for Future Generations\n| website = {{URL|https://www.appgfuturegenerations.com/}}\n}}\n\nThe '''All-Party Parliamentary Group for Future Generations''' is an informal, cross-party, group with the [[parliament of the United Kingdom]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/200224/future-generations.htm|title=House of Commons - Register Of All-Party Parliamentary Groups as at 24 February 2020: Future Generations|last=|first=|date=|website=publications.parliament.uk|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref> Its role is to raise the profile of long-term issues, protect the interests of [[future generation]]s, and provide a forum for discussion about ways to reduce short-termism in politics and policy making.\n\nThe group officially launched in 2018, with the assistance of [[Martin Rees]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/future/story/20190318-can-we-reinvent-democracy-for-the-long-term|title=Why we need to reinvent democracy for the long-term|last=Krznaric|first=Roman|website=www.bbc.com|language=en|access-date=2019-07-07}}</ref>, a member of the House of Lords, who has written extensively on the future of humanity and the potential dangers humanity might face.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1028209978|title=On the future : prospects for humanity|last=Rees, Martin J., 1942-|isbn=9780691180441|location=Princeton, New Jersey|oclc=1028209978}}</ref>\n\nThe group's secretariat is the [[Centre for the Study of Existential Risk]] at [[University of Cambridge|Cambridge University]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cser.ac.uk/news/cser-supports-new-appg/|title=CSER supports new APPG|website=www.cser.ac.uk|access-date=2019-01-16}}</ref>\n\n== Officers ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Officers<ref name=\":0\" />\n!Role\n!Name\n!Party\n|-\n|Chair & Registered Contact\n|[[Bambos Charalambous]]\n|[[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]]\n|-\n|Co-Chair\n|[[John Bird, Baron Bird|Lord Bird]]\n|Crossbench\n|-\n|Officer\n|[[Martin Rees|Lord Rees]]\n|[[Crossbencher|Crossbench]]\n|-\n|Officer\n|[[Cheryl Gillan]]\n|[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]]\n|-\n|Officer\n|[[Anna McMorrin]]\n|Labour\n|-\n|Officer\n|[[Daniel Zeichner]]\n|Labour\n|-\n|Officer\n|[[Liz Saville Roberts]]\n|[[Plaid Cymru]]\n|-\n|Officer\n|[[Caroline Lucas]]\n|[[Green Party of England and Wales|Green Party]]\n|-\n|Officer\n|[[Simon Fell (politician)|Simon Fell]]\n|Conservative\n|}\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|https://www.appgfuturegenerations.com/}}\n\n[[Category:All-Party Parliamentary Groups]]\n\n\n{{UK-poli-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{multiple issues|\n{{notability|Companies|date=March 2019}}\n{{third-party|date=March 2019}}\n}}\n{{Infobox organization\n| formation = October 2017\n| type = [[All-Party Parliamentary Group]]\n| leader_title = Chair\n| leader_name = [[Bambos Charalambous|Bambos Charalambous MP]]\n| name = All-Party Parliamentary Group for Future Generations\n| website = {{URL|https://www.appgfuturegenerations.com/}}\n}}\n\nThe '''All-Party Parliamentary Group for Future Generations''' is an informal, cross-party, group with the [[parliament of the United Kingdom]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm/cmallparty/200224/future-generations.htm|title=House of Commons - Register Of All-Party Parliamentary Groups as at 24 February 2020: Future Generations|last=|first=|date=|website=publications.parliament.uk|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref> Its role is to raise the profile of long-term issues, protect the interests of [[future generation]]s, and provide a forum for discussion about ways to reduce short-termism in politics and policy making.\n\nThe group officially launched in 2018, with the assistance of [[Martin Rees]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/future/story/20190318-can-we-reinvent-democracy-for-the-long-term|title=Why we need to reinvent democracy for the long-term|last=Krznaric|first=Roman|website=www.bbc.com|language=en|access-date=2019-07-07}}</ref>, a member of the House of Lords, who has written extensively on the future of humanity and the potential dangers humanity might face.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1028209978|title=On the future : prospects for humanity|last=Rees, Martin J., 1942-|isbn=9780691180441|location=Princeton, New Jersey|oclc=1028209978}}</ref>\n\nThe group's secretariat is the [[Centre for the Study of Existential Risk]] at [[University of Cambridge|Cambridge University]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cser.ac.uk/news/cser-supports-new-appg/|title=CSER supports new APPG|website=www.cser.ac.uk|access-date=2019-01-16}}</ref>\n\n== Officers ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Officers<ref name=\":0\" />\n!Role\n!Name\n!Party\n|-\n|Chair & Registered Contact\n|[[Bambos Charalambous]]\n|[[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]]\n|-\n|Co-Chair\n|[[John Bird, Baron Bird|Lord Bird]]\n|Crossbench\n|-\n|Officer\n|[[Martin Rees|Lord Rees]]\n|[[Crossbencher|Crossbench]]\n|-\n|Officer\n|[[Cheryl Gillan]]\n|[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]]\n|-\n|Officer\n|[[Anna McMorrin]]\n|Labour\n|-\n|Officer\n|[[Daniel Zeichner]]\n|Labour\n|-\n|Officer\n|[[Liz Saville Roberts]]\n|[[Plaid Cymru]]\n|-\n|Officers\n|[[Caroline Lucas]]\n|[[Green Party of England and Wales|Green Party]]\n|-\n|Officers\n|[[Simon Fell (politician)|Simon Fell]]\n|Conservative\n|}\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|https://www.appgfuturegenerations.com/}}\n\n[[Category:All-Party Parliamentary Groups]]\n\n\n{{UK-poli-stub}}\n", "name_user": "CRL956", "label": "safe", "comment": "changed officers to officer", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/All-Party_Parliamentary_Group_for_Future_Generations"}
